finding no pulse heroux began performing the same compression 
technique bishop had been practicing 
heroux was joined by carl ireland another instructor who 
performed compression while heroux blew air into bishops lungs 
they regained a pulse then lost it again 
the instructors were joined by anthony k scierka director of 
field operations for lampm ambulance corp and professional ambulance 
service who was at the site demonstrating his paramedic equipment 
scierka put a cardiac monitor on bishop and determined he had 
ventricular tachycardia an irregular heartbeat that keeps the 
heart from pumping blood and gave bishops heart an electric 
shock with a defibrillator 
as about 20 stunned students looked on bishops heart began 
pumping he soon regained consciousness and began talking smiling 
and thanking his rescuers 
