<TEXT>
the scrawled note by michael dukakis about a 
controversial prison project turned out to be prophetic this 
spells mucho trouble lets discuss msd 
later the massachusetts governor penned another message to his 
legal counsel on a plan to build a prison in the tiny central town 
of new braintree no further action until we discuss msd 
the democratic presidential nominee had correctly predicted the 
storm of controversy that would surround the plan but his 1985 
notes displayed something else about dukakis that has become more 
visible on the campaign trail his instinctive caution when he 
smells trouble 
that has been the dukakis management style through recent 
largely crisisfree years as governor the style born of a 
firstterm disaster has been an easy one to adopt in a state with 
a boom economy and little opposition from republicans 
but on the campaign trail as the presidential race tightens and 
he comes under relentless criticism by vice president george bush 
dukakis has given indications that he wants to turn more aggressive 
that was much in evidence when he rehired john sasso the 
campaign chief who was ousted after releasing the tape that led to 
delaware sen joseph bidens withdrawal from the presidential race 
dukakis took some heat for the decision but he got his way and 
fallout was minimized by his timing he made the announcement at 
the start of the long labor day weekend 
i dont think he sees himself as a great risktaker he 
doesnt place a high value on that said martin linsky a 
lecturer at the john f kennedy school of government who was a 
republican colleague in the state legislature 
dukakis cautious approach to the sasso affair reflected lessons 
he learned in 1975 when trying to keep a strong campaign promise 
of no new taxes he held out until forced to impose tax 
increases and spending cuts that angered both the right and left 
going down the street with him the verbal abuse he would take 
from people was quite unbelievable said thomas p oneill iii 
son of the former house speaker and dukakis lieutenant governor in 
1975 i really think he had such confidence in his ability to 
handle the deficit problem that that would have an overriding 
effect on the public relations end of the problem 
joseph grandmaison chairman of the new hampshire democratic 
party managed dukakis 1974 campaign for governor and recalls a 
politician much more willing to make snap decisions then than he is 
now back in the early 70s he was far more likely to look at a 
situation and come to an immediate conclusion about what was the 
best way to proceed he said 
the lesson was clear said paul garrity the former judge who 
pushed the administration into the boston harbor cleanup project 
once burned twice shy 
after he won back the governorship in 1982 dukakis kept a tight 
rein on news emanating from the governors office and from the many 
state agencies no press release bearing dukakis name went out 
without being personally checked by the governor press aides kept 
lists of good and bad reporters broken down by those whose 
coverage favored or hurt the administration 
hes taken more seriously the communications aspect of 
government linsky said 
the muchheralded transformation of dukakis from his early years 
in office to his two recent terms was not entirely complete linsky 
said dukakis once again this year finds himself wrestling with a 
state budget shortfall although the crisis isnt as serious as in 
dukakis first term he has had to sign a cigarette tax into law to 
help raise tax revenues 
one of the ways to think about the pattern of not dealing with 
revenue problems until fairly late in the game is that if he 
doesnt want it to be a problem he doesnt see it as a problem 
linsky said 
in 1986 dukakis used the hunkerdown approach to distance 
himself from disclosures that state officials had approved a 
10000 payment to silence a student who charged a state college 
president with sexual assault 
the governor recalled first hearing about the alleged assault 
and the payoff in january 1986 he said he told a top state 
education official to get on it and take care of it but 
dukakis did nothing further to investigate until the story 
intensified six months later 
for more than a year dukakis let two top administration 
officials handle questions on the new braintree prison issue even 
amid charges later refuted that dukakis had granted a personal 
favor to friends who owned the prison site 
he also kept a back seat when a prison furlough program that he 
deeply believed in came under fire when a convicted murderer on 
furlough terrorized a maryland couple he reversed the furlough 
policy as public opinion was reaching a crescendo 
but a cautious approach to governing that kept dukakis out of 
trouble in massachusetts hasnt translated into safety on the 
campaign trail 
early this month bush scored political points by coming to 
polluted boston harbor to highlight an example of what he called 
the consequences of excessive delay dukakis was forced to defend 
himself by saying that after a decade as governor something was 
finally being done to clean the harbor 
